## Qualitative variable compensation of Executive corporate officers

The  Board  of  Directors,  at  its  meeting  of  February/uni00A024, 2022,  on  the  recommendation  of  the  Nomination  and Remuneration Committee, set at 97.8% the overall level of achievement  of  the  four  qualitative  objectives  used  to determine  the  variable  compensation  for  2021  of  the Executive corporate officers (namely Mr. Pierre-André de Chalendar,  Chairman  and  Chief  executive  officer  from January/uni00A01  to  June/uni00A030,  2021  and  Mr.  Benoit  Bazin,  Chief operating  officer  from  January/uni00A01,  2021  to  June/uni00A030,  2021 then Chief executive officer from July/uni00A01, 2021 to December/uni00A031, 2021), as outlined above.

In particular, it took the following main achievements into consideration:

